{
  "_comment": [
    "Supakiln seccomp profile — starts from Docker default and explicitly",
    "denies syscalls the review flagged plus a few extra exploit primitives.",
    "Attached via --security-opt seccomp=/opt/supakiln/security/seccomp.json.",
    "",
    "Architecture choice: defaultAction=SCMP_ACT_ERRNO(EPERM) with an explicit",
    "ALLOW list for the set of syscalls CPython 3.12 + common language runtimes",
    "actually need. Docker's default profile is the other shape (default-allow",
    "with a deny list); we invert it so anything new the kernel adds is",
    "denied by default."
  ],
  "defaultAction": "SCMP_ACT_ERRNO",
  "defaultErrnoRet": 1,
  "archMap": [
    {
      "architecture": "SCMP_ARCH_X86_64",
      "subArchitectures": ["SCMP_ARCH_X86", "SCMP_ARCH_X32"]
    },
    {
      "architecture": "SCMP_ARCH_AARCH64",
      "subArchitectures": ["SCMP_ARCH_ARM"]
    }
  ],
