    {
      "_comment": "clone is allowed only WITHOUT namespace-creation flags. Blocks CLONE_NEWUSER/NEWNS/NEWPID/NEWIPC/NEWUTS/NEWNET/NEWCGROUP which are the classic sandbox-escape primitives.",
      "names": ["clone"],
      "action": "SCMP_ACT_ALLOW",
      "args": [
        {
          "index": 0,
          "value": 2114060288,
          "valueTwo": 0,
          "op": "SCMP_CMP_MASKED_EQ"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_comment": "clone3 gets ENOSYS (38), not EPERM. Modern glibc tries clone3 first for pthread_create; on ENOSYS it falls back to clone (which is allowed above with namespace flags masked). Returning EPERM instead breaks ThreadingHTTPServer with 'RuntimeError: can't start new thread'. This mirrors Docker's default profile behavior.",
      "names": ["clone3"],
      "action": "SCMP_ACT_ERRNO",
      "errnoRet": 38
    },
    {
